
[1]because

   BECAUSE, becauz' a compound word. [ See By and Cause.]

   By cause, or by the cause; on this account; for the cause which is
   explained in the next proposition; for the reason next explained. Thus,
   I fled, because I was afraid, is to be thus resolved; I fled, by the
   cause, for the cause, which is mentioned in the next affirmation, viz.
   I was afraid. Hence, cause being a noun, because may be regularly
   followed by of.

   The spirit is life, because of righteousness.

   Because of these cometh the wrath of God upon the children of
   disobedience.
